The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, January 05, 2003 				 Engineer in bribe bond 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Burdwan, Jan. 4: A divisional engineer of the state electricity board was arrested yesterday for allegedly taking a bribe from the owner of a cold storage in Bankura. Gopal Chandra Neogi was held by a WBSEB vigilance team. 																								Vigilance sources said Dinabandhu Garai, owner of G.M. Cold Storage, had sent a written complaint to the Bankura district magistrate and police as well as the vigilance wing in Calcutta that the engineer had demanded Rs 1.3 lakhs from him for sanctioning a system that could lower the bill of the cold storage. 
